Statement to verify:
The flyers were founded in 1967 and won consecutive stanley cup championships in 1974 and 1975, the first expansion team to do so. the team has had success in the playoffs throughout their history, making multiple appearances in the stanley cup finals. the flyers last qualified for the playoffs in 2017-18 and their most recent playoff series victory was in the 2012 eastern conference quarterfinals. considering this, it is clear that the flyers have been a strong playoff team in recent years, indicating that they are likely to make the playoffs again in April 2021.
